The only reason Agema probably went for this we-got-bent-over deal was because the other guild could have just wrongfully kept &quot;all&quot; of the loot.  Thier hands were tied.  Get &quot;some&quot; loot from the bullies that took our lunch money, or watch as everyone here flames them for complaining about being KSed.  (Yes, I'm sure from reading previous posts here, that Agema would have been full out berated on these boards for bringing these events to light, even though THEY were the victums.  Higher tier guilded loudmouths would go on and on about how they &quot;must&quot; have been wrong like they always do). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utrayvar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trayvar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 3:05:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> &quot; As Bada indicated, both guilds had capable forces zone in at roughly the same time, after which it comes down to dps.&quot;<br>
<br>
NO, it comes down to who engages first at that point.  You admit that BOTH guilds had the force present to kill said turtle at this point.  Just because 2 guilds have the force present doesn't mean they have the right to ignore first to engage and just KS a mob from someone else who has already engaged it.<br>
<br>
The kiting the mob prior to the forces being present might as well not exsist.  It didn't even take place as it can't be considered engaging.  But once BOTH guilds had sufficiant forces, neither having engaged yet, who ever starts pulling it to their camp for the kill HAS ENGAGED.  Or are you saying that ganking pulls off of someone is right?<br>
<br>
If we were all to go by your logic here:  Lets say IvM and EW are both in Kael.  EW engages AoW.  Since IvM had the force in the zone that could do AoW, they could just strole up and try to outdamage EW?  That's exactly what you just said, only the mob was a turtle and the guilds were Agema and Prism.<br>
<br>
Both guilds had the force at the time of the pull.  Agema started in on the turtle first.  Prism interfering in a DPS contest at this point is full on KSing with intent. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umandari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 3:19:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=30>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.nc.rr.com/prismites/icon1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> Except that Lodizal wasn't engaged by Agema with sufficient force.  We knew we had force zoning in (and zoned in, actually; I was the last to arrive); we couldn't know how long it would take for Agema to assemble.<br>
